articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Has the U.S. overplayed its hand by killing top Iranian general?
articles.description: Vali Nasr, a professor at the Johns Hopkins School of Advanced International Studies tells MSNBC’s David Gura why the United States may have “overplayed its hand” with the killing of top Iranian General Qasem Soleimani.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: What is the potential retaliation from Iran for Soleimani’s death?
articles.description: Iran has vowed to revenge Qasam Soleimani's death. MSNBC’s David Gura and a panel of guests discuss worries about what that could be and how other nations are responding.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Ret. Col. Wilkerson: Trump escalated situation in Iran with no plan for next step
articles.description: Retired Col. Lawrence Wilkerson explains why President Trump has escalated the situation in Iran with the killing of Soleimani.  He discusses with MSNBC’s David Gura.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Sen. Peters: What was the imminent threat Iran posed?
articles.description: Democratic Senator Gary Peters of Michigan of the Armed Services Committee says Congress needs specifics on the “imminent threat” posed by Iran that led to Trump’s decision to kill Qasam Soleimani.
